{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: condition-eps_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Condition instance conforming to the ConditionOblEuEps
    profile (EPS Condition with Obligations). Each invocation represents one
    clinical problem or diagnosis on the patient's problem list, or a sentinel
    "no known problems" record when the patient has no conditions.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: ConditionOblEuEps
    Must-support elements covered:
      category, code (with preferred text), clinicalStatus,
      onsetDateTime (or absent-reason), abatementDateTime, subject, asserter

  RELATIONSHIP TO condition-eu_fsh.twig
    Both templates share the active/inactive logic and the three-column HTML
    pattern. Key differences are documented in the comparison table below.

    ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬────────────────────────┐
    │ Aspect                           │ condition-eps        │ condition-eu           │
    ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┼────────────────────────┤
    │ Profile                          │ ConditionOblEuEps    │ ConditionEuCore        │
    │ Null test operator               │ is null (strict)     │ is not null (inverse)  │
    │ No-condition output              │ Full sentinel FSH    │ Empty HTML row only    │
    │ addHTML_tr() placement           │ Inside {% else %}    │ Before {% if %}        │
    │ addHTML_trend() placement        │ Inside {% else %}    │ After {% endif %}      │
    │ Categories emitted               │ One                  │ Two                    │
    │ condition.code structure         │ Single object only   │ Array-or-object        │
    │ preferred term override          │ Only if differs from │ Unconditionally        │
    │                                  │ .display             │ when non-empty         │
    │ clinicalStatus rule              │ Emitted              │ Not emitted            │
    │ abatementDateTime guard          │ end + inactive both  │ end non-empty only     │
    └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┴────────────────────────┘

  TWO-MODE PATTERN — `is null` STRICT TEST
    The top-level branch tests `{% if condition is null %}`.
    Note: `is null` is a strict null check, distinct from `is empty`:
      - `is null`  → true only for PHP null / Twig null (not for empty string
                     or empty array)
      - `is empty` → true for null, empty string, empty array, and zero
    The caller must pass a PHP null (not an empty array or "") to trigger
    Mode A.

  MODE A — NO KNOWN CONDITION (condition is null)
    A sentinel FSH instance is emitted carrying:
      code.coding[0] = $sct#160245001 "No current problems or disability (situation)"
      onsetDateTime.extension → data-absent-reason #unknown
    A single HTML cell "No known problems or disabilities" is emitted.
    No category or clinicalStatus rule is included in the sentinel.

  MODE B — CONDITION DATA PRESENT (condition is not null)

    PRE-CALCULATIONS (two local variables):
      activeflag — first character of condition.active (format "SYYYY-MM-DD")
                   extracted via |slice(0, 1); "1" = active, "0" = inactive.
      inactive   — boolean: `activeflag == 0` (integer equality).
      preferred  — display label: uses condition.code.preferredTerm if it is
                   non-empty AND differs from condition.code.display. This
                   two-condition guard prevents the preferred term from being
                   set when it is identical to the default display, which
                   differs from condition-eu which overrides unconditionally.

    CATEGORY
      A single category is emitted:
        * category = $condition-category#problem-list-item "Problem List Item"
      This is the EPS problem-list focus; encounter-diagnosis is not added
      (unlike condition-eu which emits both categories).

    CODE
      code.coding[0] uses explicit [0] index (one coding per condition).
      code.text is set to the resolved preferred term.

    THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE (no HEAD)
      TD 1 — Condition display: `addHTML_tdgray` when inactive, `addHTML_td`
              when active. `clinicalStatus` is emitted immediately after the
              TD 1 cell call — co-located with the activity state.
      TD 2 — Onset / period: absent-reason "?" when start is empty; otherwise
              formats `hperiod` as a local variable:
                start date alone         : "d-M-Y"
                start + end (inactive)   : "d-M-Y - d-M-Y"
              Note: abatementDateTime is only emitted when BOTH condition.end
              is non-empty AND the condition is inactive. An active condition
              with an end date will not emit abatementDateTime.
      TD 3 — Status label: "inactive" (gray) or "active" (normal cell).

    clinicalStatus PLACEMENT
      Unlike most FSH rules which appear before or after all HTML calls,
      clinicalStatus is emitted inside the TD 1 conditional block, immediately
      after `addHTML_td[gray]()`. This co-locates the FSH rule with the
      visual state it expresses:
        {% if inactive %}
        {{ addHTML_tdgray(preferred) }}
        * clinicalStatus = $condition-clinical#inactive
        {% else %}
        {{ addHTML_td(preferred) }}
        * clinicalStatus = $condition-clinical#active
        {% endif %}

    ASSERTER (conditional)
      When `asserter` is non-empty, a Reference to the asserter's role
      resource is emitted. The `asserter` object carries `.instancerole`
      (UUID) and `.name` (display string). This links the condition to the
      clinician who asserted it, typically a PractitionerRole instance.

  NARRATIVE — BODY ROWS ONLY (Pattern 1)
    Only emitHTML() is flushed inside text.div — no HEAD in the narrative.
    %%HEAD%% is empty (no addHEAD_th calls are made anywhere in this template).

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                       │ string   │ Unique resource id.                        │
  │ patient.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.              │
  │ patient.name                     │ string   │ Full display name for the subject Ref.     │
  │ condition                        │ object?  │ null → Mode A. Non-null → Mode B.         │
  │   .active                        │ string   │   Activity string "SYYYY-MM-DD"; first     │
  │                                  │          │   char is "1" (active) or "0" (inactive).  │
  │   .code.system                   │ string   │   CodeSystem URI for the condition code.   │
  │   .code.code                     │ string   │   Condition concept code.                  │
  │   .code.display                  │ string   │   Default display text.                    │
  │   .code.preferredTerm            │ string?  │   Preferred display override. Used only    │
  │                                  │          │   when non-empty AND different from        │
  │                                  │          │   .code.display.                           │
  │   .start                         │ string?  │   ISO 8601 onset date. When empty,        │
  │                                  │          │   data-absent-reason is emitted.           │
  │   .end                           │ string?  │   ISO 8601 abatement date. Emitted as     │
  │                                  │          │   abatementDateTime only when non-empty    │
  │                                  │          │   AND the condition is inactive.           │
  │ asserter                         │ object?  │   Optional asserter (clinician who        │
  │   .instancerole                  │ string   │   asserted the condition).                 │
  │   .name                          │ string   │   Asserter display name.                   │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct                — SNOMED CT; 160245001 "No current problems" (sentinel),
                          condition codes (caller-supplied)
    $condition-category — problem-list-item
    $condition-clinical — #active, #inactive

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Condition-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ConditionOblEuEps
Title: "Condition Obligations (EPS)"
Description: "Condition"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{% if condition is null %}
{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE A — NO KNOWN CONDITION
  `is null` is a strict null check — the caller must pass PHP null, not an
  empty array or empty string, to reach this branch.
  A full sentinel FSH instance is emitted carrying the SNOMED "no current
  problems" code, plus a data-absent-reason on onsetDateTime.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
* code.coding[0] = $sct#160245001 "No current problems or disability (situation)"
* subject        = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"
{# No onset date known — signal absence with data-absent-reason extension #}
* onsetDateTime.extension.url       = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* onsetDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{# Single HTML cell — no table structure needed for a sentinel value #}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td("No known problems or disabilities") }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{% else %}
{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE B — CONDITION DATA PRESENT
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── Pre-calculations ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  activeflag: extracts the first character of condition.active ("SYYYY-MM-DD")
              to determine the activity state. "1" = active, "0" = inactive.
  inactive:   boolean flag for use in conditional branches below.
  preferred:  resolves the display label — uses preferredTerm only when it is
              non-empty AND different from condition.code.display. This two-
              condition guard differs from condition-eu which overrides
              unconditionally when preferredTerm is non-empty.
#}
{% set activeflag = condition.active | slice(0, 1) %} {# "1" = active, "0" = inactive #}
{% set inactive   = activeflag == 0 %}
{% set preferred  = condition.code.display %}
{% if condition.code.preferredTerm is not empty %}
{% if condition.code.display != condition.code.preferredTerm %}
{% set preferred = condition.code.preferredTerm %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{# Category: EPS problem list only (no encounter-diagnosis, unlike condition-eu) #}
* category = $condition-category#problem-list-item "Problem List Item"

{# Code: explicit [0] index — one coding per condition #}
* code.coding[0] = {{ condition.code.system }}#{{ condition.code.code }} "{{ condition.code.display }}"
* code.text      = "{{ preferred }}"

{#
  ── TD 1: condition name + clinicalStatus ───────────────────────────────────
  Cell style reflects activity state: gray for inactive, normal for active.
  clinicalStatus FSH rule is co-located here — emitted immediately after the
  HTML cell call that reflects the same state.
#}
{% if inactive %}
{{ addHTML_tdgray(preferred) }}
* clinicalStatus = $condition-clinical#inactive
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td(preferred) }}
* clinicalStatus = $condition-clinical#active
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 2: onset / period ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  When start is absent: data-absent-reason extension on onsetDateTime; "?" in HTML.
  When start is present:
    - onsetDateTime is always emitted.
    - hperiod local variable accumulates the HTML date string.
    - abatementDateTime is only added when BOTH condition.end is non-empty AND
      the condition is inactive. An active condition with an end date does NOT
      emit abatementDateTime (differs from condition-eu which emits whenever
      end is non-empty, regardless of active state).
    - hperiod extends to "start - end" when abatement is emitted.
#}
{% if condition.start is empty %}
* onsetDateTime.extension.url       = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* onsetDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{{ addHTML_td("?") }}
{% else %}
* onsetDateTime = "{{ condition.start }}"
{% set hperiod = condition.start|date('d-M-Y') %}
{% if condition.end is not empty and inactive %}
* abatementDateTime = "{{ condition.end }}"
{% set hperiod = hperiod ~ " - " ~ condition.end|date('d-M-Y') %}
{% endif %}
{{ addHTML_tdnb(hperiod) -}}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 3: active / inactive label ───────────────────────────────────────────
  Gray cell for inactive; normal cell for active.
#}
{% if inactive %}
{{ addHTML_tdgray("inactive") -}}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("active") }}
{% endif %}

{# Patient reference #}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── Asserter (conditional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  References the PractitionerRole resource of the clinician who asserted the
  condition. Requires asserter.instancerole (UUID) and asserter.name (display).
#}
{% if asserter is not empty %}
* asserter = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ asserter.instancerole }}) "{{ asserter.name }}"
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{% endif %} {# condition is null / not null #}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative — body rows only (Pattern 1) ─────────────────────────────
  emitHTML() only — no HEAD bag populated, %%HEAD%% is empty.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
